        "ERCOT counts on an adequate supply of electric generation to meet demand and maintain capacity reserves to help support grid reliability if shortfalls occur.This section includes access to ERCOT market studies and analysis materials related to resource adequacy as well as ERCOT short- and long-term forecast reports on generation supply and demand.Reports produced prior to 2012 are located in the yearly archive section of Reports and Presentations All other archives are located at the bottom of the page.\n[...]\n## Monthly Generator Interconnection Status Report\n[...]\nView the latest public interconnection information on planned generation resources in the ERCOT Region.\n[...]\n### Resource Capacity Trend Charts Resource Capacity Trend Charts\n[...]\nCharts and accompanying data showing annual and monthly changes in resource capacity by fuel type for the ERCOT Region, incorporating both historical additions and planned projects being studied as part of the interconnection request process. The chart are updated on a monthly basis, and include natural gas, wind, solar, and battery storage resource types.\n[...]\nCapacity Changes by Fuel Type Charts December 2024 Planned Monthly\n[...]\nCapacity Changes by Fuel Type Charts December 2024\n[...]\nCapacity Changes by Fuel Type Charts November 2024 Planned Monthly\n[...]\nCapacity Changes by Fuel\n[...]\nCharts November 2024\n[...]\nCapacity Changes by Fuel Type Charts September 2024 Planned Monthly\n[...]\n) Report Capacity,\n[...]\nand Reserves (CDR) Report\n[...]\n2022 Zonal Reliability Study\n[...]\nProof-of-concept study to investigate probabilistic reliability modeling using a multi-zone representation of the ERCOT grid rather than a single system region. The study examined how a target reliability standard level (0.1 expected loss-of-load events per year) can be maintained for individual regions and the system as a whole by increasing zonal generation capacity or expanding transmission between zones.\n[...]\nJan 9, 2023 - pdf - 1.3 MB"
